Results showing the band structures and the local density of states (LDOS) projected in space, for some of the considered configurations, are presented in Fig. 3. We focus on the impurity in-gap states near the Fermi energy introduced by the Moimp atom, indicated by the areas enclosed by orange rectangles. The band structures of the most stable structures show three distinctive in-gap states, joined in two groups, labeled as regions 1 and 2 with degeneracies of one and two, respectively. Although the Moimp in these two configurations have an octahedral sulfur environment, the in-gap bands present slightly different dispersive behavior. In region 1, the band for the T-AB’ case is more dispersive than the corresponding band for the H-AA’ configuration, which is almost flat. The states in region 1 mainly have \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
